r to join our EMEA Employment Counsel team to support and help lead our growing businesses across MEA. This is the perfect opportunity to join a global legal team integral to a company engaged in cutting edge technology and focused on solving some of the biggest challenges in the world - including changing the way regulators, courts and legislators think about the future of work. Based in Johannesburg (South Africa), and in cooperation with another employment lawyer in MEA, this position will report directly to the EMEA Employment Director based in Amsterdam. WHAT YOU\u2019LL DO Advise Uber\u2019s HR team on the full range of employment matters relating to recruiting, hiring, training, performance management, compensation, benefits, and terminations primarily in South Africa. Identify and resolve employment related issues regarding Uber\u2019s business and its relationship with users of the Uber App in our MEA markets. Handle and advise on pre-litigation disputes and employment litigation. Collaborate closely with colleagues in tax, regulatory legal, product developers and policy and communications team to pre-empt employment law risks related to Uber\u2019s business, and proactive finding solutions to those issues. WHAT YOU\u2019LL NEED 5-6 years of employment law experience with preference for mix of in- house and law firm background. Fluent in written and spoken in Arabic and English (fluency in French is a plus as well) Strong academic credentials and law degree from a top law school Excellent business judgment, communication and interpersonal skills International profile and experience Be an effective and transparent communicator No ego \u2013 at Uber we work as a team, and you\u2019ll be expected to work with others in a constructive manner to achieve the goals of the business Thrive in high impact/high profile situations Enthusiastic about Uber and how we are changing the way people move PERKS Travel like a diplomat: employees are showered with Uber credits G